            <section ID="i4i_description_id_f091ba68-d84f-422b-83eb-1baffd0216c0">
               <id root="fedbf230-61df-4d7a-9c1f-7aeb45abb86b"/>
               <code codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" code="34089-3" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Proparacaine Hydrochloride Ophthalmic Solution USP, 0.5% is a local anesthetic for ophthalmic instillation. Each mL of sterile, aqueous solution contains: Active: Proparacaine Hydrochloride 5 mg (0.5%). Preservative: Benzalkonium Chloride 0.1 mg (0.01%). Inactives: Glycerin as a stabilizer, Hydrochloric Acid and/or Sodium Hydroxide may be added to adjust pH (3.5 to 6.0), and Water for Injection USP.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Proparacaine hydrochloride is designed chemically as 2-(Diethylamino)ethyl 3-amino-4-propoxybenzoate monohydrochloride. The active ingredient is represented by the structural formula:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="id_63bf5d93-cd41-4711-888d-a0d521d5817c"/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20080514"/>
               <component>
                  <observationMedia ID="id_63bf5d93-cd41-4711-888d-a0d521d5817c">
                     <text>Chemical Structure</text>
                     <value xsi:type="ED" mediaType="image/jpeg">
                        <reference value="c1e57227-6c96-4922-973e-74838ab4c795-01.jpg"/>
                     </value>
